overview: A newspaper clip of a 30-year-old movie makes our middle-aged protagonist in the middle of his peak years to look for his best childhood friend.Â The journey leads him back to his teenage years in the 1990s depression, over-generational substance abuse and past encounters.  This partly essayistic, autobiographical documentary tells the story of friendship and generational experiences while also pondering on the causes and effects of destinies in the judgmental atmosphere of our society.
title: Track Two
